{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775861918004,"sessionID":"ses_286621cb8ffel5WbNo5U839Mdp","part":{"id":"prt_d799e5922001Os5xQQAW0FXR3o","messageID":"msg_d799e2521001MMmXxydORAoCb5","sessionID":"ses_286621cb8ffel5WbNo5U839Mdp","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/router/jwt.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/router/jwt.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: /*\n2: Copyright 2026 The Volcano Authors.\n3: \n4: Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n5: you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n6: You may obtain a copy of the License at\n7: \n8:     http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n9: \n10: Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n11: distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n12: WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n13: See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n14: limitations under the License.\n15: */\n16: \n17: package router\n18: \n19: import (\n20: \t\"crypto/rand\"\n21: \t\"crypto/rsa\"\n22: \t\"crypto/x509\"\n23: \t\"encoding/pem\"\n24: \t\"fmt\"\n25: \t\"os\"\n26: \t\"time\"\n27: \n28: \t\"github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5\"\n29: \tcorev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"\n30: \tapierrors \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors\"\n31: \tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n32: \t\"k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes\"\n33: \t\"k8s.io/client-go/rest\"\n34: \t\"k8s.io/klog/v2\"\n35: )\n36: \n37: const (\n38: \trsaKeySize         = 2048\n39: \tjwtExpiration      = 5 * time.Minute\n40: \tidentitySecretName = \"picod-router-identity\"\n41: \tprivateKeyDataKey  = \"private.pem\"\n42: \tpublicKeyDataKey   = \"public.pem\"\n43: )\n44: \n45: // IdentityNamespace is the namespace where the JWT identity secret is stored.\n46: // Initialized from AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE env var or defaults to \"default\".\n47: var IdentityNamespace = \"default\"\n48: \n49: func init() {\n50: \tif ns := os.Getenv(\"AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE\"); ns != \"\" {\n51: \t\tIdentityNamespace = ns\n52: \t}\n53: }\n54: \n55: // JWTManager handles JWT key generation and token signing.\n56: type JWTManager struct {\n57: \tprivateKey *rsa.PrivateKey\n58: \tpublicKey  *rsa.PublicKey\n59: \tclientset  kubernetes.Interface\n60: }\n61: \n62: // NewJWTManager creates a new JWTManager with a generated RSA key pair.\n63: func NewJWTManager() (*JWTManager, error) {\n64: \tprivateKey, err := rsa.GenerateKey(rand.Reader, rsaKeySize)\n65: \tif err != nil {\n66: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to generate RSA key: %w\", err)\n67: \t}\n68: \n69: \treturn &JWTManager{\n70: \t\tprivateKey: privateKey,\n71: \t\tpublicKey:  &privateKey.PublicKey,\n72: \t}, nil\n73: }\n74: \n75: // GenerateToken creates a JWT with the given claims.\n76: func (m *JWTManager) GenerateToken(claims map[string]interface{}) (string, error) {\n77: \tnow := time.Now()\n78: \n79: \t// Build base claims\n80: \ttokenClaims := jwt.MapClaims{\n81: \t\t\"exp\": now.Add(jwtExpiration).Unix(),\n82: \t\t\"iat\": now.Unix(),\n83: \t\t\"iss\": \"agentcube-router\",\n84: \t}\n85: \n86: \t// Merge custom claims\n87: \tfor k, v := range claims {\n88: \t\ttokenClaims[k] = v\n89: \t}\n90: \n91: \t// Create and sign token\n92: \ttoken := jwt.NewWithClaims(jwt.SigningMethodRS256, tokenClaims)\n93: \ttokenString, err := token.SignedString(m.privateKey)\n94: \tif err != nil {\n95: \t\treturn \"\", fmt.Errorf(\"failed to sign token: %w\", err)\n96: \t}\n97: \n98: \treturn tokenString, nil\n99: }\n100: \n101: // GetPublicKeyPEM returns the public key in PEM format.\n102: func (m *JWTManager) GetPublicKeyPEM() ([]byte, error) {\n103: \tpublicKeyBytes, err := x509.MarshalPKIXPublicKey(m.publicKey)\n104: \tif err != nil {\n105: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to marshal public key: %w\", err)\n106: \t}\n107: \n108: \tpemBlock := &pem.Block{\n109: \t\tType:  \"PUBLIC KEY\",\n110: \t\tBytes: publicKeyBytes,\n111: \t}\n112: \n113: \treturn pem.EncodeToMemory(pemBlock), nil\n114: }\n115: \n116: // GetPrivateKeyPEM returns the private key in PEM format.\n117: func (m *JWTManager) GetPrivateKeyPEM() ([]byte, error) {\n118: \tprivateKeyBytes := x509.MarshalPKCS1PrivateKey(m.privateKey)\n119: \n120: \tpemBlock := &pem.Block{\n121: \t\tType:  \"RSA PRIVATE KEY\",\n122: \t\tBytes: privateKeyBytes,\n123: \t}\n124: \n125: \treturn pem.EncodeToMemory(pemBlock), nil\n126: }\n127: \n128: // TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret attempts to store the JWT keys in a Kubernetes secret\n129: // or load them if the secret already exists. Returns nil if not running in-cluster.\n130: func (m *JWTManager) TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret() error {\n131: \t// Try to get in-cluster config\n132: \tconfig, err := rest.InClusterConfig()\n133: \tif err != nil {\n134: \t\tklog.Warningf(\"Not running in Kubernetes cluster, using ephemeral JWT keys: %v\", err)\n135: \t\treturn nil\n136: \t}\n137: \n138: \t// Create clientset\n139: \tclientset, err := kubernetes.NewForConfig(config)\n140: \tif err != nil {\n141: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"failed to create Kubernetes client: %w\", err)\n142: \t}\n143: \n144: \tm.clientset = clientset\n145: \n146: \t// Get or create the secret\n147: \treturn m.createOrLoadSecret()\n148: }\n149: \n150: func (m *JWTManager) createOrLoadSecret() error {\n151: \t// Try to create the secret\n152: \tprivatePEM, err := m.GetPrivateKeyPEM()\n153: \tif err != nil {\n154: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"failed to encode private key: %w\", err)\n155: \t}\n156: \n157: \tpublicPEM, err := m.GetPublicKeyPEM()\n158: \tif err != nil {\n159: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"failed to encode public key: %w\", err)\n160: \t}\n161: \n162: \tsecret := &corev1.Secret{\n163: \t\tObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n164: \t\t\tName:      identitySecretName,\n165: \t\t\tNamespace: IdentityNamespace,\n166: \t\t\tLabels: map[string]string{\n167: \t\t\t\t\"app\":       \"agentcube\",\n168: \t\t\t\t\"component\": \"router\",\n169: \t\t\t},\n170: \t\t},\n171: \t\tType: corev1.SecretTypeOpaque,\n172: \t\tData: map[string][]byte{\n173: \t\t\tprivateKeyDataKey: privatePEM,\n174: \t\t\tpublicKeyDataKey:  publicPEM,\n175: \t\t},\n176: \t}\n177: \n178: \t_, err = m.clientset.CoreV1().Secrets(IdentityNamespace).Create(nil, secret, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n179: \tif err != nil {\n180: \t\tif apierrors.IsAlreadyExists(err) {\n181: \t\t\t// Secret exists, load the keys\n182: \t\t\treturn m.loadExistingSecret()\n183: \t\t}\n184: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"failed to create JWT secret: %w\", err)\n185: \t}\n186: \n187: \tklog.Infof(\"Created JWT identity secret '%s' in namespace '%s'\", identitySecretName, IdentityNamespace)\n188: \treturn nil\n189: }\n190: \n191: func (m *JWTManager) loadExistingSecret() error {\n192: \tsecret, err := m.clientset.CoreV1().Secrets(IdentityNamespace).Get(nil, identitySecretName, metav1.GetOptions{})\n193: \tif err != nil {\n194: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"failed to get existing JWT secret: %w\", err)\n195: \t}\n196: \n197: \tprivatePEM, ok := secret.Data[privateKeyDataKey]\n198: \tif !ok {\n199: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"existing JWT secret missing private key data\")\n200: \t}\n201: \n202: \treturn m.loadPrivateKeyPEM(privatePEM)\n203: }\n204: \n205: func (m *JWTManager) loadPrivateKeyPEM(pemData []byte) error {\n206: \tblock, _ := pem.Decode(pemData)\n207: \tif block == nil {\n208: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"failed to decode PEM block\")\n209: \t}\n210: \n211: \tprivateKey, err := x509.ParsePKCS1PrivateKey(block.Bytes)\n212: \tif err != nil {\n213: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"failed to parse private key: %w\", err)\n214: \t}\n215: \n216: \tm.privateKey = privateKey\n217: \tm.publicKey = &privateKey.PublicKey\n218: \n219: \tklog.Infof(\"Loaded existing JWT keys from secret '%s'\", identitySecretName)\n220: \treturn nil\n221: }\n\n(End of file - total 221 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"/*\nCopyright 2026 The Volcano Authors.\n\nLicensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\nyou may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\nYou may obtain a copy of the License at\n\n    http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n\nUnless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\ndistributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\nWITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\nSee the License for the specific language governing permissions and\nlimitations under the License.\n*/\n\npackage router\n\nimport (\n\t\"crypto/rand\"","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/router/jwt.go","time":{"start":1775861917982,"end":1775861918003}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775861918006,"sessionID":"ses_286621cb8ffel5WbNo5U839Mdp","part":{"id":"prt_d799e5e6b001kE1C11stkPzEPl","messageID":"msg_d799e2521001MMmXxydORAoCb5","sessionID":"ses_286621cb8ffel5WbNo5U839Mdp","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/router/config.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/router/config.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: /*\n2: Copyright 2026 The Volcano Authors.\n3: \n4: Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n5: you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n6: You may obtain a copy of the License at\n7: \n8:     http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n9: \n10: Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n11: distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n12: WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n13: See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n14: limitations under the License.\n15: */\n16: \n17: package router\n18: \n19: // LastActivityAnnotationKey is the annotation key for last activity timestamp.\n20: const LastActivityAnnotationKey = \"agentcube.volcano.sh/last-activity\"\n21: \n22: // Config holds the router server configuration.\n23: type Config struct {\n24: \t// Port is the HTTP server port (default: \"8080\")\n25: \tPort string\n26: \n27: \t// Debug enables debug mode for Gin\n28: \tDebug bool\n29: \n30: \t// EnableTLS enables TLS for the server\n31: \tEnableTLS bool\n32: \n33: \t// TLSCert is the path to the TLS certificate file\n34: \tTLSCert string\n35: \n36: \t// TLSKey is the path to the TLS key file\n37: \tTLSKey string\n38: \n39: \t// MaxConcurrentRequests limits concurrent requests (0 = unlimited at flag level;\n40: \t// NewServer coerces to 1000 when <= 0)\n41: \tMaxConcurrentRequests int\n42: }\n43: \n44: // DefaultConfig returns a Config with sensible defaults.\n45: func DefaultConfig() *Config {\n46: \treturn &Config{\n47: \t\tPort:                  \"8080\",\n48: \t\tDebug:                 false,\n49: \t\tEnableTLS:             false,\n50: \t\tMaxConcurrentRequests: 1000,\n51: \t}\n52: }\n\n(End of file - total 52 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"/*\nCopyright 2026 The Volcano Authors.\n\nLicensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\nyou may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\nYou may obtain a copy of the License at\n\n    http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n\nUnless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\ndistributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\nWITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\nSee the License for the specific language governing permissions and\nlimitations under the License.\n*/\n\npackage router\n\n// LastActivityAnnotationKey is the annotation key for last activity timestamp.\nconst LastActivityAnnotationKey = \"agentcube.volcano.sh/last-activity\"","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/router/config.go","time":{"start":1775861917985,"end":1775861918005}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775861918009,"sessionID":"ses_286621cb8ffel5WbNo5U839Mdp","part":{"id":"prt_d799e639f001uEgoiCavXSvTkM","messageID":"msg_d799e2521001MMmXxydORAoCb5","sessionID":"ses_286621cb8ffel5WbNo5U839Mdp","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-010/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-010/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-010: Router 会话管理 - Delta Specification\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-010  \n6: **Module:** `pkg/router`  \n7: **Language:** Go  \n8: **Size:** M  \n9: **Base Spec:** [deployment/client-go.md](../../deployment/client-go.md), [session-routing/design.md](../../session-routing/design.md), [session-store/design.md](../../session-store/design.md)\n10: \n11: The Router Session Management component provides session lifecycle management, state tracking, and session affinity routing for the AgentCube HTTP reverse proxy. It integrates with the session store for persistence and uses the Kubernetes client-go library for sandbox metadata retrieval.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Requirements\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: Session Resolution\n18: \n19: The system SHALL resolve sandbox sessions by session ID through the SessionManager interface.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Resolve existing session from store\n22: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with session ID `sess-abc-123` exists in the session store\n23: - **WHEN** `SessionManager.GetSandboxBySession()` is called with the session ID\n24: - **THEN** the system SHALL return the `SandboxInfo` with all session metadata\n25: \n26: #### Scenario: Session not found in store\n27: - **GIVEN** no sandbox exists with session ID `sess-missing-456`\n28: - **WHEN** `SessionManager.GetSandboxBySession()` is called\n29: - **THEN** the system SHALL return `store.ErrNotFound` error\n30: \n31: #### Scenario: Session lookup populates from Workload Manager on cache miss\n32: - **GIVEN** a session exists in Kubernetes but not in the local store\n33: - **AND** the Workload Manager API returns valid sandbox info for the session\n34: - **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySession()` is called with the session ID\n35: - **THEN** the system SHALL query the Workload Manager and return the sandbox info\n36: \n37: #### Scenario: Workload Manager unavailable during session lookup\n38: - **GIVEN** the session store does not contain the requested session\n39: - **AND** the Workload Manager API is unreachable\n40: - **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySession()` is called\n41: - **THEN** the system SHALL return an error indicating the Workload Manager is unavailable\n42: \n43: ---\n44: \n45: ### Requirement: Session State Tracking\n46: \n47: The system SHALL track and update session activity timestamps for lifecycle management.\n48: \n49: #### Scenario: Update last activity timestamp on request\n50: - **GIVEN** an active session with session ID `sess-active-789`\n51: - **WHEN** a request is routed through the proxy to that session\n52: - **THEN** the system SHALL call `store.UpdateSessionLastActivity()` with the current timestamp\n53: \n54: #### Scenario: Activity update failures are logged but non-blocking\n55: - **GIVEN** an active session and a failing store connection\n56: - **WHEN** the activity update fails\n57: - **THEN** the system SHALL log the error and continue processing the request\n58: \n59: #### Scenario: Session expiry is tracked\n60: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with `ExpiresAt` set to a future timestamp\n61: - **WHEN** the session is stored via `StoreSandbox()`\n62: - **THEN** the system SHALL add the session to the expiry index with the expiration timestamp\n63: \n64: #### Scenario: Expired sessions are identifiable\n65: - **GIVEN** sessions with various expiration timestamps exist in the store\n66: - **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes()` is called with `before=now`\n67: - **THEN** the system SHALL return only sessions where `ExpiresAt <= now`\n68: \n69: ---\n70: \n71: ### Requirement: Session Affinity Routing\n72: \n73: The system SHALL maintain session affinity by consistently routing requests to the same sandbox instance.\n74: \n75: #### Scenario: Route request to correct sandbox endpoint\n76: - **GIVEN** a session with entry points `[{Protocol: \"http\", Endpoint: \"10.0.1.5:8080\", Path: \"/\"}]`\n77: - **WHEN** an invocation request is received for that session\n78: - **THEN** the reverse proxy SHALL forward the request to `10.0.1.5:8080`\n79: \n80: #### Scenario: Session ID header injection\n81: - **GIVEN** a valid session is resolved for an incoming request\n82: - **WHEN** the response is returned to the client\n83: - **THEN** the response SHALL include header `x-agentcube-session-id: <session-id>`\n84: \n85: #### Scenario: Request with missing session ID\n86: - **GIVEN** a request without a valid session identifier\n87: - **WHEN** the router processes the request\n88: - **THEN** the system SHALL return HTTP 400 with error message \"session ID required\"\n89: \n90: ---\n91: \n92: ### Requirement: Session Lifecycle Integration\n93: \n94: The system SHALL integrate with the session lifecycle events from the Workload Manager.\n95: \n96: #### Scenario: Handle session creation notification\n97: - **GIVEN** a new sandbox is created via the Workload Manager\n98: - **WHEN** the Session Manager receives the creation event\n99: - **THEN** the system SHALL store the session info via `StoreSandbox()`\n100: \n101: #### Scenario: Handle session deletion notification\n102: - **GIVEN** an existing session in the store\n103: - **WHEN** the Workload Manager sends a deletion notification\n104: - **THEN** the system SHALL remove the session via `DeleteSandboxBySessionID()`\n105: \n106: #### Scenario: Handle session update notification\n107: - **GIVEN** an existing session with outdated metadata\n108: - **WHEN** the Workload Manager sends an update with new entry points\n109: - **THEN** the system SHALL update the session via `UpdateSandbox()`\n110: \n111: ---\n112: \n113: ### Requirement: JWT Session Claims\n114: \n115: The system SHALL generate JWT tokens with session-specific claims for authenticated routing.\n116: \n117: #### Scenario: Generate JWT with session ID claim\n118: - **GIVEN** a session ID `sess-jwt-001` and a `JWTManager` with valid RSA keys\n119: - **WHEN** `GenerateToken(map[string]interface{}{\"session_id\": \"sess-jwt-001\"})` is called\n120: - **THEN** the system SHALL return a signed JWT containing claim `session_id: sess-jwt-001`\n121: \n122: #### Scenario: JWT includes standard claims\n123: - **GIVEN** a `JWTManager` initialized with valid keys\n124: - **WHEN** a token is generated\n125: - **THEN** the token SHALL include `exp`, `iat`, and `iss: \"agentcube-router\"` claims\n126: \n127: #### Scenario: JWT expiration is enforced\n128: - **GIVEN** a JWT generated with 5-minute expiration\n129: - **WHEN** the token is validated after expiration\n130: - **THEN** the validation SHALL fail with an expiration error\n131: \n132: #### Scenario: JWT signing with stored keys\n133: - **GIVEN** Kubernetes cluster is accessible\n134: - **WHEN** `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret()` is called\n135: - **THEN** the system SHALL create or load the RSA key pair from Secret `picod-router-identity`\n136: \n137: ---\n138: \n139: ### Requirement: Session Metadata Management\n140: \n141: The system SHALL manage session metadata including kind, namespace, name, and status.\n142: \n143: #### Scenario: Store session with complete metadata\n144: - **GIVEN** a `SandboxInfo` with Kind=\"AgentRuntime\", Namespace=\"default\", Name=\"runtime-1\", Status=\"Running\"\n145: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox()` is called\n146: - **THEN** the system SHALL persist all metadata fields\n147: \n148: #### Scenario: Retrieve session metadata\n149: - **GIVEN** a stored session with complete metadata\n150: - **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID()` is called\n151: - **THEN** the system SHALL return the `SandboxInfo` with all original metadata intact\n152: \n153: #### Scenario: List inactive sessions\n154: - **GIVEN** sessions with varying last activity timestamps\n155: - **WHEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes()` is called with a threshold time\n156: - **THEN** the system SHALL return sessions where `lastActivity < threshold`\n157: \n158: ---\n159: \n160: ### Requirement: Error Handling\n161: \n162: The system SHALL handle session-related errors gracefully with appropriate error codes.\n163: \n164: #### Scenario: Session not found error\n165: - **GIVEN** a request for a non-existent session\n166: - **WHEN** the session lookup fails\n167: - **THEN** the system SHALL return HTTP 404 with code `SANDBOX_NOT_FOUND`\n168: \n169: #### Scenario: Store unavailable error\n170: - **GIVEN** the session store is unreachable\n171: - **WHEN** a session operation is attempted\n172: - **THEN** the system SHALL return HTTP 503 with code `SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE`\n173: \n174: #### Scenario: Invalid session ID format\n175: - **GIVEN** a request with malformed session ID containing invalid characters\n176: - **WHEN** the session ID is validated\n177: - **THEN** the system SHALL return HTTP 400 with code `VALIDATION_FAILED`\n178: \n179: ---\n180: \n181: ## Changes to Base Specification\n182: \n183: ### Modified Store Interface (from session-store/design.md)\n184: \n185: The base store interface is extended to support session management operations:\n186: \n187: | Method | Change | Description |\n188: |--------|--------|-------------|\n189: | `UpdateSessionLastActivity` | **No change** | Used by router to track session activity |\n190: | `ListInactiveSandboxes` | **No change** | Used for idle session detection |\n191: | `ListExpiredSandboxes` | **No change** | Used for expired session cleanup |\n192: \n193: ### SessionManager Interface (new)\n194: \n195: ```go\n196: type SessionManager interface {\n197:     GetSandboxBySession(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, namespace string, name string, kind string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n198: }\n199: ```\n200: \n201: ---\n202: \n203: ## New Interfaces\n204: \n205: ### SessionManager\n206: \n207: ```go\n208: // SessionManager provides session resolution and lifecycle management.\n209: type SessionManager interface {\n210:     // GetSandboxBySession resolves a sandbox by session ID.\n211:     // On cache miss, queries the Workload Manager API.\n212:     GetSandboxBySession(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, namespace string, name string, kind string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n213: }\n214: \n215: // manager implements SessionManager.\n216: type manager struct {\n217:     storeClient     store.Store\n218:     workloadMgrAddr string\n219:     httpClient      *http.Client\n220: }\n221: ```\n222: \n223: ### JWTManager\n224: \n225: ```go\n226: // JWTManager handles RSA key generation and JWT token signing.\n227: type JWTManager struct {\n228:     privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey\n229:     publicKey  *rsa.PublicKey\n230:     clientset  kubernetes.Interface\n231: }\n232: \n233: // Methods:\n234: // - NewJWTManager() (*JWTManager, error)\n235: // - GenerateToken(claims map[string]interface{}) (string, error)\n236: // - TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret(ctx context.Context) error\n237: ```\n238: \n239: ---\n240: \n241: ## Modified Interfaces\n242: \n243: ### Server struct (session-routing/design.md)\n244: \n245: The `Server` struct includes session management:\n246: \n247: ```go\n248: type Server struct {\n249:     config         *Config\n250:     engine         *gin.Engine\n251:     httpServer     *http.Server\n252:     sessionManager SessionManager    // NEW: Session management\n253:     storeClient    store.Store\n254:     httpTransport  *http.Transport\n255:     jwtManager     *JWTManager       // NEW: JWT token management\n256: }\n257: ```\n258: \n259: ---\n260: \n261: ## Behavioral Changes\n262: \n263: | Behavior | Before | After |\n264: |----------|--------|-------|\n265: | Session lookup | Direct store only | Store + Workload Manager fallback |\n266: | Session activity tracking | Not tracked | Updated on each request |\n267: | JWT generation | Not supported | RSA-signed JWT with session claims |\n268: | Session affinity | Basic routing | Header injection + consistent routing |\n269: \n270: ---\n271: \n272: ## Dependencies\n273: \n274: | Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n275: |------------|---------|---------|\n276: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store` | Local | Session persistence |\n277: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | Local | Shared types |\n278: | `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | Latest | JWT token signing |\n279: | `k8s.io/client-go` | `v0.34.1` | Kubernetes Secret storage for keys |\n280: | `golang.org/x/net/http2` | Latest | HTTP/2 transport configuration |\n281: \n282: ---\n283: \n284: ## File Index\n285: \n286: | Path | Purpose |\n287: |------|---------|\n288: | `pkg/router/session_manager.go` | SessionManager implementation |\n289: | `pkg/router/jwt.go` | JWTManager and token generation |\n290: | `pkg/router/server.go` | Server with session integration |\n291: | `pkg/router/handlers.go` | HTTP handlers with session resolution |\n292: \n293: ---\n294: \n295: ## API Endpoints Summary\n296: \n297: | Method | Path | Description |\n298: |--------|------|-------------|\n299: | GET/POST | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path` | Route to AgentRuntime with session affinity |\n300: | GET/POST | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path` | Route to CodeInterpreter with session affinity |\n301: \n302: ---\n303: \n304: ## Migration Notes\n305: \n306: - The `SessionManager` interface replaces direct store access for session lookups\n307: - JWT tokens are now required for authenticated Workload Manager communication\n308: - Session activity tracking is enabled by default; no migration needed for existing sessions\n309: - RSA keys are automatically generated on first startup if not present in Kubernetes Secrets\n310: \n311: ---\n312: \n313: ## Acceptance Criteria Summary\n314: \n315: 1. **Session Resolution**: Sessions can be resolved from both store and Workload Manager fallback\n316: 2. **Activity Tracking**: Last activity timestamp is updated on each routed request\n317: 3. **Session Affinity**: Requests are consistently routed to the same sandbox endpoint\n318: 4. **JWT Integration**: Tokens are generated with proper session claims and expiration\n319: 5. **Error Handling**: Appropriate HTTP status codes and error messages for all failure scenarios\n\n(End of file - total 319 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-010: Router 会话管理 - Delta Specification\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-010  \n**Module:** `pkg/router`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M  \n**Base Spec:** [deployment/client-go.md](../../deployment/client-go.md), [session-routing/design.md](../../session-routing/design.md), [session-store/design.md](../../session-store/design.md)\n\nThe Router Session Management component provides session lifecycle management, state tracking, and session affinity routing for the AgentCube HTTP reverse proxy. It integrates with the session store for persistence and uses the Kubernetes client-go library for sandbox metadata retrieval.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Session Resolution\n\nThe system SHALL resolve sandbox sessions by session ID through the SessionManager interface.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-010/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775861917987,"end":1775861918006}}}}
