{"type":"text","timestamp":1775861933280,"sessionID":"ses_286621cb8ffel5WbNo5U839Mdp","part":{"id":"prt_d799ea1fd001u33m3j0Tur24U9","messageID":"msg_d799e8af10015z55sbelJ1coas","sessionID":"ses_286621cb8ffel5WbNo5U839Mdp","type":"text","text":"Now I have a complete understanding of the codebase. Let me write the comprehensive delta-spec.md for AR-011 with GIVEN/WHEN/THEN scenarios.","time":{"start":1775861933279,"end":1775861933279}}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1775862007453,"sessionID":"ses_286621cb8ffel5WbNo5U839Mdp","part":{"id":"prt_d799f48100013MMVO3912eNGHB","messageID":"msg_d799e8af10015z55sbelJ1coas","sessionID":"ses_286621cb8ffel5WbNo5U839Mdp","type":"text","text":" Namespace","time":{"start":1775862007447,"end":1775862007447}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775862007490,"sessionID":"ses_286621cb8ffel5WbNo5U839Mdp","part":{"id":"prt_d799ea4e1001uNQkvbsEOzwwZi","messageID":"msg_d799e8af10015z55sbelJ1coas","sessionID":"ses_286621cb8ffel5WbNo5U839Mdp","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:11","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-011/delta-spec.md","content":"# AR-011: Router JWT 认证与签发 - Delta Specification\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-011  \n**Module:** `pkg/router`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M  \n**Base Spec:** [deployment/client-go.md](../../deployment/client-go.md), [pkg/router/jwt.go](../../pkg/router/jwt.go)\n\nThe Router JWT Authentication and Issuance component provides RSA-based JWT token generation, signing, and key management for the AgentCube router. It enables secure authentication between the router and the Workload Manager by generating signed JWT tokens with session-specific claims, while persisting RSA key pairs in Kubernetes Secrets for cluster-wide accessibility.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: RSA Key Pair Generation\n\nThe system SHALL generate cryptographically secure RSA key pairs for JWT signing.\n\n#### Scenario: Generate new RSA key pair on initialization\n- **GIVEN** a fresh router instance starting without existing keys\n- **WHEN** `NewJWTManager()` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL generate a 2048-bit RSA key pair\n- **AND** return a `JWTManager` with the private and public keys initialized\n\n#### Scenario: RSA key generation uses secure random source\n- **GIVEN** the router requires a new JWT signing key\n- **WHEN** the RSA key is generated using `rsa.GenerateKey(rand.Reader, 2048)`\n- **THEN** the key SHALL be generated using cryptographically secure random source\n- **AND** the private key SHALL be suitable for RS256 signing\n\n#### Scenario: Handle RSA generation failure\n- **GIVEN** the system is unable to generate RSA keys due to resource constraints\n- **WHEN** `NewJWTManager()` is called and key generation fails\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return an error with message \"failed to generate RSA key\"\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: JWT Token Generation and Signing\n\nThe system SHALL generate and sign JWT tokens with configurable claims using RS256 algorithm.\n\n#### Scenario: Generate token with custom claims\n- **GIVEN** a `JWTManager` initialized with valid RSA keys\n- **AND** a claims map containing `{\\\"session_id\\\": \\\"sess-abc-123\\\", \\\"user\\\": \\\"test-user\\\"}`\n- **WHEN** `GenerateToken(claims)` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return a signed JWT string containing all custom claims\n\n#### Scenario: JWT includes standard claims automatically\n- **GIVEN** a `JWTManager` with valid RSA keys\n- **WHEN** any token is generated via `GenerateToken()`\n- **THEN** the token SHALL include the following standard claims:\n  - `exp`: expiration time (current time + 5 minutes)\n  - `iat`: issued at time (current timestamp)\n  - `iss`: issuer (\"agentcube-router\")\n\n#### Scenario: JWT uses RS256 signing algorithm\n- **GIVEN** a `JWTManager` with RSA private key\n- **WHEN** `GenerateToken()` is called with any claims\n- **THEN** the token SHALL be signed using `jwt.SigningMethodRS256`\n- **AND** the signature SHALL be verifiable with the corresponding public key\n\n#### Scenario: Handle signing failure\n- **GIVEN** a `JWTManager` with corrupted or invalid private key\n- **WHEN** `GenerateToken()` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return an error with message \"failed to sign token\"\n\n#### Scenario: Token expiration is configurable via claims override\n- **GIVEN** a `JWTManager` with valid keys\n- **AND** a claims map containing a custom `exp` value\n- **WHEN** `GenerateToken(claims)` is called\n- **THEN** the custom expiration SHALL override the default 5-minute expiration\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: RSA Key PEM Encoding\n\nThe system SHALL provide methods to export RSA keys in standard PEM format.\n\n#### Scenario: Export public key in PEM format\n- **GIVEN** a `JWTManager` initialized with an RSA key pair\n- **WHEN** `GetPublicKeyPEM()` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return the public key encoded as PKIX PEM format\n- **AND** the PEM block type SHALL be \"PUBLIC KEY\"\n\n#### Scenario: Export private key in PEM format\n- **GIVEN** a `JWTManager` initialized with an RSA key pair\n- **WHEN** `GetPrivateKeyPEM()` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return the private key encoded as PKCS#1 PEM format\n- **AND** the PEM block type SHALL be \"RSA PRIVATE KEY\"\n\n#### Scenario: PEM encoding for key storage\n- **GIVEN** keys need to be stored in Kubernetes Secrets\n- **WHEN** `GetPublicKeyPEM()` and `GetPrivateKeyPEM()` are called\n- **THEN** the returned byte slices SHALL be valid UTF-8 strings\n- **AND** they SHALL be parseable by standard PEM decoders\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Kubernetes Secret Key Storage\n\nThe system SHALL persist and retrieve RSA keys from Kubernetes Secrets for cluster-wide access.\n\n#### Scenario: Create new secret when none exists\n- **GIVEN** the router is running in a Kubernetes cluster\n- **AND** no secret named `picod-router-identity` exists in the configured namespace\n- **WHEN** `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret()` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL create a new Secret with:\n  - Name: `picod-router-identity`\n  - Namespace: `$AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` (or \"default\")\n  - Labels: `app=agentcube`, `component=router`\n  - Data keys: `private.pem`, `public.pem`\n\n#### Scenario: Load existing keys from secret\n- **GIVEN** a secret `picod-router-identity` already exists in the namespace\n- **AND** the secret contains valid `private.pem` and `public.pem` data\n- **WHEN** `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret()` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL load the existing keys into the `JWTManager`\n- **AND** the loaded keys SHALL replace the ephemeral keys\n\n#### Scenario: Handle non-cluster environment gracefully\n- **GIVEN** the router is NOT running in a Kubernetes cluster\n- **WHEN** `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret()` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL log a warning message\n- **AND** return nil (no error) to continue with ephemeral keys\n\n#### Scenario: Handle Kubernetes client creation failure\n- **GIVEN** the router is running in-cluster but cannot create Kubernetes client\n- **WHEN** `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret()` attempts to create the clientset\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return an error with message \"failed to create Kubernetes client\"\n\n#### Scenario: Handle secret creation failure\n- **GIVEN** the router has valid Kubernetes client\n- **AND** secret creation fails for reasons other than AlreadyExists\n- **WHEN** attempting to create the JWT secret\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return an error with message \"failed to create JWT secret\"\n\n#### Scenario: Handle malformed key data in existing secret\n- **GIVEN** an existing secret with invalid or corrupted `private.pem` data\n- **WHEN** `loadExistingSecret()` attempts to parse the key\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return an error indicating key parsing failure\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: JWT Key Loading from PEM\n\nThe system SHALL be able to parse and load RSA private keys from PEM-encoded data.\n\n#### Scenario: Load private key from valid PEM data\n- **GIVEN** valid PKCS#1 RSA private key PEM data\n- **WHEN** `loadPrivateKeyPEM()` is called with the PEM bytes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL parse and set the private key\n- **AND** derive and set the corresponding public key\n\n#### Scenario: Handle invalid PEM block\n- **GIVEN** PEM data that cannot be decoded\n- **WHEN** `loadPrivateKeyPEM()` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return an error with message \"failed to decode PEM block\"\n\n#### Scenario: Handle invalid PKCS#1 key data\n- **GIVEN** PEM data with valid structure but invalid key content\n- **WHEN** `loadPrivateKeyPEM()` attempts to parse the key\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return an error with message \"failed to parse private key\"\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Namespace Configuration\n\nThe system SHALL support configurable namespace for JWT secret storage.\n\n#### Scenario: Default namespace is \"default\"\n- **GIVEN** the `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` environment variable is not set\n- **WHEN** the router package is initialized\n- **THEN** `IdentityNamespace` SHALL default to \"default\"\n\n#### Scenario: Namespace from environment variable\n- **GIVEN** the `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` environment variable is set to \"agentcube-system\"\n- **WHEN** the router package is initialized\n- **THEN** `IdentityNamespace` SHALL be set to \"agentcube-system\"\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Token Validation Support\n\nThe system SHALL provide capabilities to validate JWT tokens using the stored public key.\n\n#### Scenario: Validate token signature\n- **GIVEN** a JWT token signed by the `JWTManager`'s private key\n- **AND** the corresponding public key is available\n- **WHEN** the token is validated using the public key\n- **THEN** the signature SHALL be verified successfully\n\n#### Scenario: Reject token with invalid signature\n- **GIVEN** a JWT token signed with a different key\n- **WHEN** validation is attempted with the current public key\n- **THEN** the validation SHALL fail with a signature error\n\n#### Scenario: Reject expired token\n- **GIVEN** a JWT token that has exceeded its `exp` claim time\n- **WHEN** the token is validated\n- **THEN** the validation SHALL fail with an expiration error\n\n---\n\n## Changes to Base Specification\n\nNo modifications to existing interfaces. This AR adds new JWT management capabilities.\n\n---\n\n## New Interfaces\n\n### JWTManager\n\n```go\n// JWTManager handles RSA key generation, JWT token signing, and key persistence.\ntype JWTManager struct {\n    privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey    // RSA private key for signing\n    publicKey  *rsa.PublicKey     // RSA public key for verification\n    clientset  kubernetes.Interface // Kubernetes client for secret operations\n}\n```\n\n#### Methods\n\n| Method | Signature | Description |\n|--------|-----------|-------------|\n| `NewJWTManager` | `func NewJWTManager() (*JWTManager, error)` | Creates new JWTManager with generated RSA key pair |\n| `GenerateToken` | `func (m *JWTManager) GenerateToken(claims map[string]interface{}) (string, error)` | Creates and signs JWT with custom claims |\n| `GetPublicKeyPEM` | `func (m *JWTManager) GetPublicKeyPEM() ([]byte, error)` | Returns public key in PKIX PEM format |\n| `GetPrivateKeyPEM` | `func (m *JWTManager) GetPrivateKeyPEM() ([]byte, error)` | Returns private key in PKCS#1 PEM format |\n| `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret` | `func (m *JWTManager) TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret() error` | Stores or loads keys from Kubernetes Secret |\n\n---\n\n## Modified Interfaces\n\nNone. This AR introduces new functionality without modifying existing interfaces.\n\n---\n\n## Behavioral Changes\n\n| Behavior | Before | After |\n|----------|--------|-------|\n| JWT signing | Not supported | RS256-signed JWT with configurable claims |\n| Key persistence | Ephemeral only | Kubernetes Secret storage with fallback |\n| Key generation | None | 2048-bit RSA key generation on startup |\n| Token standard claims | None | exp, iat, iss auto-populated |\n| Cross-pod key sharing | Not possible | Via Kubernetes Secret in configured namespace |\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|---------|\n| `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | v5.x | JWT token creation and signing |\n| `k8s.io/client-go` | v0.34.1 | Kubernetes client for Secret operations |\n| `k8s.io/api/core/v1` | v0.34.1 | Secret type definitions |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1` | v0.34.1 | Kubernetes metadata types |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors` | v0.34.1 | Kubernetes API error handling |\n| `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Latest | Structured logging |\n| `crypto/rsa` | Standard library | RSA key generation |\n| `crypto/x509` | Standard library | Key encoding/decoding |\n| `encoding/pem` | Standard library | PEM format handling |\n| `crypto/rand` | Standard library | Secure random number generation |\n\n---\n\n## File Index\n\n| Path | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `pkg/router/jwt.go` | JWTManager implementation with key generation, token signing, and secret storage |\n| `pkg/router/errors.go` | JWT-specific error types (`JWTSigningError`) |\n| `pkg/router/config.go` | Configuration constants (e.g., `IdentityNamespace` initialization) |\n\n---\n\n## Constants\n\n| Constant | Value | Description |\n|----------|-------|-------------|\n| `rsaKeySize` | `2048` | RSA key bit length |\n| `jwtExpiration` | `5 * time.Minute` | Default token expiration duration |\n| `identitySecretName` | `\"picod-router-identity\"` | Kubernetes Secret name for key storage |\n| `privateKeyDataKey` | `\"private.pem\"` | Secret data key for private key |\n| `publicKeyDataKey` | `\"public.pem\"` | Secret data key for public key |\n| `IdentityNamespace` | `\"default\"` or `$AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` | Namespace for JWT secret storage |\n\n---\n\n## API Endpoints Summary\n\nThis AR provides library functionality; no HTTP endpoints are directly exposed.\n\n| Consumer | Usage |\n|----------|-------|\n| SessionManager | JWT tokens for Workload Manager authentication |\n| Router Server | Token generation for session claims |\n\n---\n\n## Migration Notes\n\n- **New dependency**: Add `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` to go.mod\n- **RBAC requirement**: Router requires permission to create/get Secrets in the target namespace\n- **Secret naming**: Uses `picod-router-identity` Secret name; ensure no conflicts\n- **Namespace configuration**: Set `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` env var for non-default namespace\n- **Key rotation**: To rotate keys, delete the `picod-router-identity` Secret; new keys will be generated\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria Summary\n\n1. **Key Generation**: RSA-2048 keys are generated on `NewJWTManager()` with secure random source\n2. **Token Creation**: `GenerateToken()` produces valid RS256-signed JWTs with standard and custom claims\n3. **Key Persistence**: Keys are stored in and loaded from Kubernetes Secret `picod-router-identity`\n4. **PEM Encoding**: Keys can be exported in standard PEM format for external use\n5. **Error Handling**: All failure scenarios return descriptive errors without panicking\n6. **Namespace Support**: Secret namespace is configurable via `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` environment variable\n7. **Non-cluster Fallback**: Gracefully handles non-Kubernetes environments with ephemeral keys\n8. **Token Validation**: Generated tokens can be validated using the stored public key\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/router/jwt.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":75,"character":53},"end":{"line":75,"character":64}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/modernize#any"},"source":"any","message":"interface{} can be replaced by any"},{"range":{"start":{"line":87,"character":2},"end":{"line":87,"character":16}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/modernize#mapsloop"},"source":"mapsloop","message":"Replace m[k]=v loop with maps.Copy"},{"range":{"start":{"line":177,"character":65},"end":{"line":177,"character":68}},"severity":2,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://staticcheck.dev/docs/checks/#SA1012"},"source":"SA1012","message":"do not pass a nil Context, even if a function permits it; pass context.TODO if you are unsure about which Context to use"},{"range":{"start":{"line":191,"character":68},"end":{"line":191,"character":71}},"severity":2,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://staticcheck.dev/docs/checks/#SA1012"},"source":"SA1012","message":"do not pass a nil Context, even if a function permits it; pass context.TODO if you are unsure about which Context to use"}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/router/config.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/router/session_manager.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/router/doc.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/router/errors.go":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-011/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-011/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775862007458,"end":1775862007486}}}}
