{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775862028359,"sessionID":"ses_286621cb8ffel5WbNo5U839Mdp","part":{"id":"prt_d79a0137b0014PdpbwQeA37Nrg","messageID":"msg_d799fc6fa001Ffeoq24Lhqhhed","sessionID":"ses_286621cb8ffel5WbNo5U839Mdp","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:12","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-011/delta-spec.md","limit":50},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-011/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-011: Router JWT 认证与签发 - Delta Specification\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-011  \n6: **Module:** `pkg/router`  \n7: **Language:** Go  \n8: **Size:** M  \n9: **Base Spec:** [deployment/client-go.md](../../deployment/client-go.md), [pkg/router/jwt.go](../../pkg/router/jwt.go)\n10: \n11: The Router JWT Authentication and Issuance component provides RSA-based JWT token generation, signing, and key management for the AgentCube router. It enables secure authentication between the router and the Workload Manager by generating signed JWT tokens with session-specific claims, while persisting RSA key pairs in Kubernetes Secrets for cluster-wide accessibility.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Requirements\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: RSA Key Pair Generation\n18: \n19: The system SHALL generate cryptographically secure RSA key pairs for JWT signing.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Generate new RSA key pair on initialization\n22: - **GIVEN** a fresh router instance starting without existing keys\n23: - **WHEN** `NewJWTManager()` is called\n24: - **THEN** the system SHALL generate a 2048-bit RSA key pair\n25: - **AND** return a `JWTManager` with the private and public keys initialized\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: RSA key generation uses secure random source\n28: - **GIVEN** the router requires a new JWT signing key\n29: - **WHEN** the RSA key is generated using `rsa.GenerateKey(rand.Reader, 2048)`\n30: - **THEN** the key SHALL be generated using cryptographically secure random source\n31: - **AND** the private key SHALL be suitable for RS256 signing\n32: \n33: #### Scenario: Handle RSA generation failure\n34: - **GIVEN** the system is unable to generate RSA keys due to resource constraints\n35: - **WHEN** `NewJWTManager()` is called and key generation fails\n36: - **THEN** the system SHALL return an error with message \"failed to generate RSA key\"\n37: \n38: ---\n39: \n40: ### Requirement: JWT Token Generation and Signing\n41: \n42: The system SHALL generate and sign JWT tokens with configurable claims using RS256 algorithm.\n43: \n44: #### Scenario: Generate token with custom claims\n45: - **GIVEN** a `JWTManager` initialized with valid RSA keys\n46: - **AND** a claims map containing `{\\\"session_id\\\": \\\"sess-abc-123\\\", \\\"user\\\": \\\"test-user\\\"}`\n47: - **WHEN** `GenerateToken(claims)` is called\n48: - **THEN** the system SHALL return a signed JWT string containing all custom claims\n49: \n50: #### Scenario: JWT includes standard claims automatically\n\n(Showing lines 1-50 of 325. Use offset=51 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-011: Router JWT 认证与签发 - Delta Specification\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-011  \n**Module:** `pkg/router`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M  \n**Base Spec:** [deployment/client-go.md](../../deployment/client-go.md), [pkg/router/jwt.go](../../pkg/router/jwt.go)\n\nThe Router JWT Authentication and Issuance component provides RSA-based JWT token generation, signing, and key management for the AgentCube router. It enables secure authentication between the router and the Workload Manager by generating signed JWT tokens with session-specific claims, while persisting RSA key pairs in Kubernetes Secrets for cluster-wide accessibility.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: RSA Key Pair Generation\n\nThe system SHALL generate cryptographically secure RSA key pairs for JWT signing.\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-011/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775862028339,"end":1775862028356}}}}
